	Switch configuration 
================================
192.168.1.5 for PC0, 192.168.1.6 for PC1

Click Switch0, then select the CLI tab.
     enable
     conf t
     Set the switch hostname (hostname LOCAL-SWITCH)
     7.	Set a Message of the Day (MOTD) banner
(banner motd # Unauthorized access is forbidden #)
     8.	Set an enable password (enable secret cisco)
     9.	Encrypt all passwords (service password-encryption)
     10.	Assign an IP address to the switch’s VLAN interface
                      interface Vlan1
                      ip address 10.0.0.1 255.0.0.0
                      no shut
•	interface Vlan1 → Selects the virtual LAN interface.
•	ip address → Assigns IP so the switch can be managed remotely via Telnet/SSH.
•	no shut → Enables the interface (it’s shutdown by default).
11.	Exit configuration mode (exit – exit – exit)
Purpose: Returns to the main prompt and saves your work.

12.	Config next switch with IP address 10.0.0.2 / 255.0.0.0


